title: For Sale:  Browning BAR Mark II Safari with BOSS in .300 Win Mag
postcontent:
After having this gun sitting in the safe for a few years, I’ve finally decided to part with it because it seems such a waste for it not to be used and appreciated.  If you’ve never shot a BAR, especially with a BOSS, you’ve missed one of the sweetest shooting semi-autos in the world (IMO).  The BOSS is Browning’s shooting optimization system that allows you to tune the rifle in seconds based on the specific factory ammo that you’re shooting, and it works.  This thing has less recoil than any high-powered rifle I’ve ever shot.  Browning claims 30-50% recoil reduction and one-hole shot groups at 100 yds.

The gun itself is in “as new” condition and was rated by H&H in OKC as 100%.  It has only had 18 rounds fired thru it at the range and does not have a flaw of any kind on it.  It has a 3x-9x x 40 mm Burris Fullfield II lifetime warranty scope, and comes with the original case, all the original paperwork, lock and tools, nice leather sling, and 22 rounds of ammo.
